Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HumanoidObject
    Interface that Humanoid uses to override methods.
    Object2D
    Interface that sets up methods for GameObject to use.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Animation
    This class allows each object's sprite list to be run every tick of a timer, making it move like an animation.
    Block
    Block class.
    FireTrap
    Allows us to create firetraps and load images for the explosion.
    Frame
    Class used for frames in each animation.
    GameMap
    GameMap procedurally generates a map that is 1.5 times bigger than the actual screen.
    GameObject
    This class implements object2D since we want our game objects to use those methods specified, such as intersects and getBoundingRectangle.
    GamePanel
    GamePanel holds the game, along with the Keyevents to make the player move, and uses it's parent, GUI, to keep track of variables.
    GUI
    GUI class creates the settings window, initializes map, player, and sounds, creates actual game window, and creates scrollpane which lets us follow the player around.
    Heading
    Heading class is used by both player and zombies to determine which way they are facing, both currently and next.
    Humanoid
    This class makes the basic layout for the player class and the zombie class.
    LineWalkZombie  
    Location
    Location class holds all methods necessary for finding an object's location on the map.
    MasterZombie
    Sets up the master zombie since his sprite is different, as well as gives him a "special power".
    Player
    The player class takes care of the animation, the movement, the current direction the sprite is moving, and collisions.
    RandomWalkZombie
    Sets up the random walk zombies and their animation sprites
    Shadow
    Created by scnaegl on 9/20/15.
    SoundLoader
    Loads the sounds to be played from the zombies, firetraps, and player sprites
    Sprite
    Used to make the different sprites that the game uses like the zombies and player.
    StartGame
    starts the game and gets everything going
    Tile  
    Zombie
    Sets up everything that a zombie has, such as smell, speed, decision rate and how the sprite will move.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    TileType
    An enum that specifies exactly what kind of tiles are used in the map.
